\n\nI'm now outlining the structure of `BlueprintGenerator.tsx`. I'll create a multi-step wizard, making sure to include clear progress indicators. This will give a premium feel. Phase 1 will gather \"Enterprise Context\", then \"Strategy & Maturity\". Phase 3 is \"Priorities\", followed by \"Contact Verification\", and finally the interactive \"AI Blueprint\" phase. I'm focusing on the input fields for each phase.\n\n\n**Implementing Step Transitions**\n\nI'm now integrating Framer Motion to create smooth transitions between the wizard steps in `BlueprintGenerator.tsx`. I've verified the project utilizes `motion/react` and am making sure this is consistently applied. I am defining state variables for each input field and the current step to facilitate animated transitions between them. I'm focusing on user engagement, and a great UX.\n\n\n**Defining Input Forms**\n\nI'm now integrating the selectable options for each wizard step. In \"Enterprise Context,\" I've added Industry, Company Size (with size-based labels), and an optional Budget selector. I'm focusing on user-friendly design and logical groupings. I'll need to define the state for each selection and handle the form submission for the next step.\n\n\n**Integrating Input Selection**\n\nI'm now integrating the selectable options for each wizard step.  In step one, I've added options for geography. Step two now has AI Journey, Data Readiness, Leadership Commitment and the Biggest Challenge.  For Step 3, I'm integrating the options for Top Priorities (multi-select), with logic for a maximum selection of three choices.\n\n\n**Refining Verification Process**\n\nI'm now implementing the email and OTP verification within the Blueprint Generator. I've built the email input with validation and the \"Request Secure Access Code\" button, which triggers the OTP input field and a placeholder message. The mock OTP system won't call any backends.\n\n\n**Refining Result Display**\n\nI'm now focused on the final Blueprint report UI. It'll be designed with a luxury dashboard feel. I'm prioritizing a progress meter for the AI Readiness Score and dynamic display for the Top 5 opportunities. I'll also add category badges with glow effects, and am writing a helper function in `lib/blueprint-data.ts` to return these 5 opportunities with elegant descriptions.\n\n\n**Refining AI Opportunities**\n\nI'm now generating custom AI opportunities. For all industry types, I'm integrating five premium, tailored opportunities, including a general default. I'll need to define the logic to display the best opportunity based on the biggest challenge, incorporating options such as \"GFF AI Enterprise Agent Factory™,\" and \"GFF Sovereign Knowledge Graph™\" for highly customized and premium AI solutions.\n\n\n**Defining Business Impact Elements**\n\nI'm now incorporating detailed business impact projections into the blueprint. I will include clear ROI metrics and customization by company size. Expected impact statements will use phrases like \"Modelled Impact\" with disclaimers. I'm focusing on defining business value, and presenting it to the user.\n\n\\n\\n\nI'm focusing on defining the 90-day roadmap in `lib/blueprint-data.ts`. The roadmap will be in three phases, each with specific milestones: Foundation, Pilot, and Scale. I will now refactor `lib/blueprint-data.ts`, to include all necessary data structures. I will completely replace the content.\n\n\n**Refactoring Data Definitions**\n\nI'm now completely restructuring `lib/blueprint-data.ts` to include complete data structures and re-export necessary elements. I am also working on the data for each industry. This includes the `BlueprintAnswers` type, industry options, and company size ranges. I'm focusing on making a clear schema.\n\n\n**Refining Roadmap Integration**\n\nI'm now integrating the 90-day roadmap into the `BlueprintResult` structure. The roadmap is now split into Foundation, Pilot, and Scale phases. Each phase will include its specific mile